race.comment: TOTTORI (8) is a lightly-raced five-year-old that pulled up with a minor issue after his first-up run. That was his first appearance in over 12 months so there is certain to be good fitness improvement in the horse. He's drawn the inside and gets the services of Todd Pannell, both of which look positives for a horse with tactical speed. He can track the speed and fight out the finish. DAPPER DON (7) has run well in both starts since breaking his maiden. He can roll forward with the 3kg claim and take some catching. MURPH (5) looks ready to win. He has been getting back and savaging the line in recent starts. He's another who is drawn low and maps to potentially settle closer. MINE ALL MINE (4) and THE WIRRULLA BOY (2) line up fresh and both deserve some thought for wider plays.
